Dick Ebersol Resigns as Chief of NBC Sports Group After 22 Years in Post

-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 
2011-05-19T18:16:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/dick-ebersol-resigns-as-chief-of-nbc-sports-group-after-22-years-in-post.html
Dick Ebersol resigned at chairman of
the NBC Sports group, ending a 22-year run as head of the
division, parent  NBC Universal  said.  Mark Lazarus, president of NBC Sports Cable Group, will
succeed him, New York-based NBC said today in a statment.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
